HEADWORD: Pyrargyrite
<hw>Py*rar"gy*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ fire +
<?/ silver.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Ruby silver; dark red silver
ore. It is a sulphide of antimony and silver, occurring in rhombohedral
crystals or massive, and is of a dark red or black color with a metallic
adamantine luster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

